Prerequsite
To run the program, you need to install following python packages if you don't have it:
-nltk: http://www.nltk.org/install.html
-scikit-learn: pip3 install -U scikit-learn
-scipy: pip3 install -U scipy
-tweepy: http://docs.tweepy.org/en/v3.5.0/install.html

How to run the program: demo.py
Grant execuation : chmod +x ./demo.py

Steps:
"Please give how many data you want to train: " - Give the number of dataset you want to train
"Please give the model you want to use to train (nb or svm) :" - input 'nb' or 'svm'
"Please give how many real time tweets you want to collect: " - input number of real time tweets you want to collect

Then you will see the output like:
"RT @tedcruz: .@carlyfiorina: Donald and Hillary would both be disastrous for this nation. They’re flip sides of the same coin https://t.co/… => neg"

Sample
$ ./demo.py
Please give how many data you want to train: 100
Processing tweets ...
Please give the model you want to use to train (nb or svm) : svm
Train on 80 instances, Test on 20 instances using Support Vector Machine...
Training complete.
